  "meta": {
    "notes": "STOA AI Factory — /stoa Slash Command Handler.\n\nHandles /stoa commands from Slack:\n  - help: show available commands + user tier\n  - status: fetch 5 recent GHA workflow runs\n  - scan: trigger claude-autopilot-scan.yml (admin only)\n  - implement CAB-XXXX: dispatch L3 pipeline via repository_dispatch (admin only)\n\nPattern: immediate 200 ACK (Slack <3s requirement) → deferred response via response_url POST.\n\nAccess control tiers (same as n8n-slack-interactive.json):\n  - admin (SLACK_ADMIN_USERS): all commands\n  - allowed (SLACK_ALLOWED_USERS): help + status only\n  - readonly: 403\n  - Backward compatible: empty SLACK_ADMIN_USERS = all allowed users are admins\n\nRequired environment variables (Docker Compose .env):\n  - SLACK_SIGNING_SECRET: Slack app signing secret\n  - SLACK_ALLOWED_USERS: Comma-separated Slack user IDs (optional)\n  - SLACK_ADMIN_USERS: Comma-separated Slack user IDs for admin tier (optional)\n\nRequired credentials:\n  - GitHub PAT (httpHeaderAuth, id: github-pat)\n\nSlack App setup:\n  Slash Commands → /stoa → Request URL: https://n8n.gostoa.dev/webhook/stoa-slash-command"
  }
